<HL>
   Canadian July Retail Sales Rise
</HL>
<DATE>
09/24/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B10
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian retail sales in July rose 0.8% from
June, Statistics Canada, a federal agency, said.
   In June, retail sales rose 0.9%. Apart from gains in June
and July, retail sales have been weak in 1990.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The July gain was partly attributed to a rise in
supermarket sales.
</TEXT>
