WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B13B
</SO>
<CO>
   RPCX UPJ
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
DRUG MANUFACTURERS (DRG)
</IN>
<LP>
   EATONTOWN, N.J. -- Roberts Pharmaceutical Corp. said it
purchased the rights to several brands in the U.S., Canada,
Britain and Ireland from Upjohn Co., a health care company
based in Kalamazoo, Mich. Terms weren't disclosed.
   Roberts, which acquires, develops and markets
pharmaceuticals, acquired several respiratory and analgesic
brands, including Cheracol and Orthoxicol cough syrups,
Pyrroxate cold and allergy medicine, P-A-C aspirin tablets,
and Haltran, an ibuprofen product.
</LP>
